messages.message: Hey team! When opening up localhost, I've been getting a blank screen and "Internal Server Error" after multiple master branch pulls and recompilations both locally and in Docker. I was wondering if anyone had insight into this problem
any error in the console?
just showing the failed GET request and a warning abt ssl certificates, although i've used localhost without secure connection before
There is a bug happening right now that's making some apps not render, but it should produce a blank screen, not an internal server error. What failed GET request is this?
what does `prov status lite` show?
it's just for getting https://localhost and I make sure all services are up before each try
anything interesting in the logs for webapp or server-nginx?
soo this is an error from webapp, and nothing that I notice from server-nginx
hm, this smells like a protobuf incompatibility, let me see if I get the same

weird, it seems to work for me (I get the white page issue that @Jessica is debugging, but that happens after your error would come up I think) â€” can you send me the logs that show up around that error?
sure thing, like a screenshot or the file or?
either one :slightly_smiling_face:
you can also try to `make update-python` from `tools/devtools`
ooh, ill try that after my meeting!
here's some before the error as welll

I also see this: `[2022-10-05 15:43:05,307] [MainProcess/MainThread] {/Users/acomis/Desktop/WorkRepos/instabase/webserver/webapp/build/py/instabase/utils/web/flask_util.py:79} ERROR - [a3c35c338a36429a] - User () not found`

try in an incognito window or clearing your browser cookies
oki
so in an incognito tab, I'm able to log in and `https://localhost/account/login` becomes a white screen with the following console error
cool, that is the expected error that jessica is working on :slightly_smiling_face: so just clear your browser cookies and you should be good to go
ahh, thanks :slightly_smiling_face:

I believe this is the PR to fix the monaco issue: https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/31370

so once that gets merged you can pull master again and hopefully it should work
(unless it breaks again when you log in again...)
